<plot>Children don't just watch Adventureville, and they don't just play it either-they get to do both, experiencing Adventureville first hand! Instead of zoning out in front of the tube, with Adventureville, couch potatoes turn into active learners. They get to decide whether they want to sing a song, learn about manners, or learn the difference between right and left. Kids learn to think for themselves, and since there are no wrong answers, their choices are always positively reinforced.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?024355</url></doc>
